Data Overview 2

Data Source

The data used for this analysis was sourced from Kaggle.com.The data was collected from customer transaction records through integrated e-commerce platforms and retail point-of-sale systems at the time of order placement, shipment, and payment.


Key Metrics




System Architecture
The project workflow involves analyzing Electronics sale data to identify trends and contributing factors, gathering relevant data from Kaggles.com , cleansing and preprocessing the dataset, applying machine learning models to predict accident severity, performing in-depth analysis using DAX and Power BI, visualizing key insights through interactive dashboards, and providing data-driven recommendations to improve road safety and reduce accident severity.





Data Features

The dataset includes essential metrics such as Churn Date, Customer Segment, Customer Risk Status (High/Medium/Low), and Total Sales, each represented with intuitive visual cues for clarity. Additionally, a 'Data Dictionary' is included, visually mapping relationships between attributes like Customer Behavior and Churn Status, which highlights key factors such as GPM and the Churn Rate, critical for analyzing customer retention trends and predicting future churn patterns.
